  <h2 id="technical-seo">Technical SEO Checks (20+)</h2>

  <p>
    Technical SEO forms the foundation of your site's crawlability and indexability. These checks ensure search engines can access and understand your content.
  </p>

  <h3 id="status-codes">Status Code Validation</h3>

  <p>Crawlix categorizes HTTP status codes and flags issues:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>4xx errors</strong> (404, 403, 410) - Pages that return client errors indicate broken links or access issues</li>
    <li><strong>5xx errors</strong> (500, 502, 503) - Server errors that prevent crawling</li>
    <li><strong>Soft 404 detection</strong> - Pages returning 200 OK but containing "not found" content (sneaky!)</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="callout callout-tip">
    <strong>Pro tip:</strong> Soft 404s are particularly problematic because search engines may index these error pages. Crawlix detects them by analyzing page content for error indicators.
  </div>

  <h3 id="canonicals">Canonical Tag Analysis</h3>

  <p>Crawlix validates canonical tags with these checks:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Missing canonical</strong> - No canonical tag present (risk of duplicate content)</li>
    <li><strong>Multiple canonicals</strong> - More than one canonical tag (confuses search engines)</li>
    <li><strong>Invalid canonical URL</strong> - Malformed or non-resolving canonical target</li>
    <li><strong>Self-referencing canonical</strong> - Points to itself (usually correct, but flagged for review)</li>
    <li><strong>Canonical chain</strong> - Canonical points to a page with a different canonical</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 id="redirects">Redirect Chain Analysis</h3>

  <p>Redirect chains waste crawl budget and dilute link equity:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Redirect chains</strong> - More than 2 hops in a redirect sequence</li>
    <li><strong>Excessive redirects</strong> - Chains with 3+ hops (recommended max: 3)</li>
    <li><strong>Redirect loops</strong> - Infinite redirect cycles</li>
    <li><strong>Mixed redirect types</strong> - Chains combining 301, 302, and meta refreshes</li>
  </ul>

