    <li><strong>Crawl depth</strong> - Pages >3 clicks from homepage flagged</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="on-page-seo">On-Page SEO Checks (25+)</h2>

  <p>
    On-page SEO checks analyze the content and meta elements that directly influence how search engines understand and rank your pages.
  </p>

  <h3 id="title-tags">Title Tag Validation</h3>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Missing title</strong> - No title tag present</li>
    <li><strong>Too short</strong> - Less than 30 characters (not descriptive enough)</li>
    <li><strong>Too long</strong> - More than 60 characters (may be truncated)</li>
    <li><strong>Generic title</strong> - Contains placeholder text like "Home" or "Untitled"</li>
    <li><strong>Multiple titles</strong> - More than one title tag</li>
    <li><strong>Duplicate titles</strong> - Same title used across multiple pages</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 id="meta-descriptions">Meta Description Validation</h3>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Missing description</strong> - No meta description tag</li>
    <li><strong>Too short</strong> - Less than 70 characters</li>
    <li><strong>Too long</strong> - More than 160 characters</li>
    <li><strong>Multiple descriptions</strong> - More than one meta description</li>
    <li><strong>Duplicate descriptions</strong> - Same description across pages</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 id="heading-hierarchy">Heading Hierarchy</h3>

  <p>Proper heading structure helps both users and search engines understand content organization:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Missing H1</strong> - Every page should have exactly one H1</li>
    <li><strong>Multiple H1s</strong> - More than one H1 tag</li>
    <li><strong>H1 too short/long</strong> - Should be descriptive but concise</li>
    <li><strong>H1 matches title</strong> - Exact duplicate (missed optimization opportunity)</li>
    <li><strong>Missing H2</strong> - Content-rich pages should use subheadings</li>
    <li><strong>Skipped heading levels</strong> - H3 without H2, H4 without H3</li>
    <li><strong>Empty headings</strong> - Heading tags with no text content</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 id="open-graph">Open Graph & Social Tags</h3>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Missing OG title</strong> - No <code>og:title</code> tag</li>
    <li><strong>Missing OG description</strong> - No <code>og:description</code> tag</li>
    <li><strong>Missing OG image</strong> - No <code>og:image</code> tag (critical for social sharing)</li>
    <li><strong>Missing Twitter Card</strong> - No Twitter-specific meta tags</li>
    <li><strong>Incomplete OG tags</strong> - Partial Open Graph implementation</li>
  </ul>

